
The small clearing at the edge of the pond was filled with the heavy thuds of metal striking earth. A handful of people bustled about seeking perfect placement for the dozens of plants that would soon fill the holes being carved into the ground. Astilbe, ferns, azaleas, camellias, hydrangea and hostas by the bucketful ringed the edges of the void deep in the Vines Botanical Gardens in Loganville. When they were done, those few people had created the Relay For Life's Healing Garden for those living with or those who have lost a loved one to cancer. The shade garden is open to the public. 

